# Module Conventions

Each feature lives under `src/modules/<Name>/` with three files:

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `<name>.routes.js` | Express `Router`, wire validators → controllers |
| `<name>.controller.js` | Business logic, wrapped in `ErrorCatch` |
| `<name>.Validation.js` | Joi schemas as middleware |

## Controller pattern

```js
import { ErrorCatch } from "../../utils/ErrorCatch.js";

export const Action = ErrorCatch(async (req, res) => {
  // ...
  res.status(200).json({ message: "...", success: true });
});
```

## Routes pattern

```js
import { Router } from "express";
const router = Router();
router.post("/path", SomeValidation, SomeController);
export default router;
```

## Rules

- Wrap every async handler with `ErrorCatch`
- Put feature-specific Joi in the module’s `*.Validation.js`, not shared middleware
- Mount the router in `src/app.router.js` (e.g. `app.use("/auth", authRoutes)`)
- Use lowercase request body fields consistent with models (`name`, `email`, `password`, `phone`)
